[4] Guinea-Bissau reports suspected Ebola case
Date: Fri 12 Dec 2014
Source: Medical Xpress, AFP (Agence France-Presse) report [edited]
http://medicalxpress.com/news/2014-12-guinea-bissau-ebola-case.html


Guinea-Bissau reports suspected Ebola case
------------------------------------------
A man who entered Guinea-Bissau from neighbouring Guinea the day after the border reopened is being treated for suspected Ebola, a medical official said on Fri [12 Dec 2014]. The traveller was running a temperature and put under surveillance as he tried to pass through the Fulamori border crossing on Wed [10 Dec2014]. He took advantage of lax security among border guards to escape observation and boarded a bus headed for the eastern city of Gabu, where he was apprehended.

"He had a temperature higher than 39 C (102 F). It is for this reason that we have isolated him pending further analysis of his case," said Gilda Helena De Almeida Vieira, head nurse at a health post in the western village of Buruntuma; 8 fellow passengers were quarantined, said Vieira.... -- more

